QueryText: ASKED ABOUT ONGANIC FARMING AND DISEASE MANAGEMENT IN SEASON FLOWERS
KccAns: ANSWERED IN DETAILED: PRACTICE SOIL SOLARIZATION- SOIL PREPARATION-MAKE THE SOIL BED IN SMALL PIECES, AND THEN SPRAY SOME AMOUNT OF FORMALIN IN SOIL BED, COVER THE BED WITH BLACK POLYTHEEN (PLASTIC) THEN KEEP IT FOR 1-2 WEEKS DURING SUNNY DAYS. FIELD IS READY FOR CULTIVATION AFTER 2 WEEKS. SEED TREATMENT CAN BE DONE WITH GARLIC EXTRACT, CRUST THE GARLIC IN CLEAN CONTAINER AND MIX WITH SOME AMOUNT OF WATER. SOAK THE SEEDS IN SOLUTION FOR 30 MINUTES THEN SHADE DRY FOR ONE HOUR OR SEED TRATMENT WITH F-STOP (TRICHODERMA HARZIANUM)@ 2g IN 1 LITER OF WATER. PRACTICE THIS BEFORE CULTIVATION. REMOVE INFECTED LEAVES AND FLOWERS FROM THE FIELD, IT MAY SPREAD TO ANY OTHER PLANT. PRESENTLY SPRAY BAVISTIN @ 1g IN 1 LITER OF WATER AT 10 DAYS INTERVAL FOR TWO TIMES.

QueryText: QUERY ABOUT BLOSSOM END ROT OF TOMATO
KccAns: SUGGESTED TO SPRAY BLOSSOM END ROT SPRAY @ 2ML PER LITERS OF WATER OR CALCIUM CHLORIDE @ 2ML PER LITER OF WATERS AND SPRAY AMISTER @ 1 TO 1.5 ML PER LITER OF WATER ATLEAST 2 SPRAY AT 7 DAYS INTERVAL. REMOVE ALL THE INFECTED PLANTS FROM THE FIELD TO AVOID SPREAD OF DISEASES. ALWAYS PRACTICE SEED TREATMENT WITH BIOAGENTS LIKE NEEM, GARLIC PASTE, GINGER PASTE,HOT WATER TREATMENT ETC.  BEFORE CULTIVATION TO AVOID SEED-BORNE DISEASES.

KccAns: suggested: seed treatment with hot water treatment @ 51 degree celcius for 10 minutes after that shade dry for 30 minutes,and seed treatment with garlic paste and soil solarization

QueryText: QUER ABOUT SEED AND SOIL TREATMENT WITH CHEMICAL OR BIOAGENTS
KccAns: SUGGESTED: SEED TREATMENT WITH HOT WATER TREATMENT @ 51 DEGREE CELCIUS FOR 10 MINUTES, AND SEED TREATMENT WITH GARLIC PASTE, SOIL SOLARIZATION CAN BE DONE BY PREPARING SOIL BED PROPERLY, KEEP FOR 2 DAYS UNDER THE SUN, THEN SPRAY SOIL FUMIGANTS OVER THE BEDS AND COVER WITH BLACK POLYETHENE TO ABSORB THE HEAT. KEEP IT FOR 2 TO 4 WEEKS UNDER THE HOT SUMMER WEATHER TEMPT. SHOULD REACH ATLEAST 28 DEGREE CELCIUS. THEN IT IS READY FOR SOWING. CHEMICAL TREATMENT FOR LATE BLIGHT OF TOMATO/POTATO- YOU CAN SPRAY MANCOZEB OR ZINEB 2 ML PER LITER OF WATER ATLEAST 3 OR 4 SPRAY AT 10 DAYS INTERVAL. PRACTICE CROP ROTATION AFTER HARVESTIONG FOR 1 TO 2 YEARS TO REMOVE PATHOGENS FROM THE FIELD. FOR ANY FURTHER QUERY YOU CAN VISIT NEAREST AGRI OFFICE IN YOUR BLOCK. KINDLY CALL KISAN CALL CENTER TO CHECK THE LATEST WEATHER REPORT UPDATES
